# AI service mode polymorphism

## Rule
rate-agent and qa-agent run in three modes: `web` (FastAPI), `polling` (Datastore queue poller), `job` (Cloud Run Job). New AI logic must work in **all three** modes without special-casing.

## Why
Both services compose the same core pipeline under different entry points. Logic that works in `web` but not in `polling` or `job` creates silent regressions in the batch path, where most production traffic actually runs.

## Constraints
- Business logic takes a task payload (Pydantic model) and produces a result — never a FastAPI `Request` or a Datastore entity directly.
- Mode-specific adapters live at the entry point: HTTP handler → payload, poller → payload, job main → payload.
- Logging includes a `run_mode` field so operators can distinguish paths.
- Tests cover the core pipeline once; per-mode tests cover only the adapter layer.

## Examples

### Good
> `service/extractor.py` has `def extract(task: Task) -> Result`. `main_web.py`, `main_poller.py`, `main_job.py` each parse their trigger to `Task` and call `extract`.

### Bad
> `service/extractor.py` accesses `request.json()` or `datastore_entity.key` — coupled to one mode.

